<item>
            <title>[MNG-4126] [regression] Properties defined in profiles.xml of parent are not inherited during multimodule build</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-4126</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Next multimodule project structure is given:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/&lt;br/&gt;
--/parent/&lt;br/&gt;
------------pom.xml           - this is aggregator which holds reference to child module in &amp;lt;modules&amp;gt; section. &lt;br/&gt;
------------profiles.xml      - contains custom property  &quot;test.property=test-property-value&quot;.        &lt;br/&gt;
--/child/&lt;br/&gt;
------------/src/main/resources/child.properties  - contains property &quot;some.useful.property=@test.property@&quot;. This property should be filtered using value defined   -                                                                                      in profiles.xml.&lt;br/&gt;
------------/pom.xml                                                    - contains reference to parent/pom.xml in &amp;lt;parent&amp;gt; pom section.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, when I run &quot;mvn clean install&quot; using parent/pom.xml I expect that in child/target/child.properties I will see filtered property &quot;some.useful.property=test-property-value&quot;. But property remains unfiltered. src/main/resources in child/pom.xml are marjed as filtered.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, when I run the same command from &quot;child&quot; folder then property is filtered with right value. In single module build all works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maven 2.0.10 behaves in expected way and filters this property in both cases.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See attached test case.&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
